 250 years—is infused throughout with Cicero’s thought and spirit.Complete with the original Latin on facing pages and an inviting introduction, Michael Fontaine’s engaging translation makes this searching exploration of grief available to readers once again.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBereavement. 0aConsolation. 0aGrief. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAdolescence.  aAgamedes.  aAquifer.  aAtheism.  aBou Craa.  aCarbon cycle.  aCenozoic.  aCetacea.  aChaldea.  aChemical reaction.  aChristian mortalism.  aClimate change.  aCrantor (mythology).  aCritical thinking.  aCrocodilia.  aCrop circle.  aCrying.  aDeep sea.  aDrinking water.  aEctotherm.  aElectricity.  aFauna.  aFertilisation.  aFertilizer.  aFossil fuel.  aFresh water.  aGenerosity.  aGenre.  aGnaeus (praenomen).  aGrandparent.  aGreatness.  aGreenhouse gas.  aGrief.  aGroundwater flow.  aGroundwater.  aHerodotus.  aHistorical fiction.  aHomily.  aHydrophiinae.  aIchthyosaur.  aIn Death.  aInner peace.  aIntegument.  aLactation.  aLate Triassic.  aLiterature.  aMammal.  aMan alone (stock character).  aMarine biology.  aMarine mammal.  aMarine reptile.  aMesozoic.  aMetabolism.  aMicrostructure.  aMining (military).  aMisery (novel).  aMisfortune (folk tale).  aMosasaur.  aNeglect.  aOgallala Aquifer.  aOral tradition.  aOur Children.  aPelagic zone.  aPetrarch.  aPhosphorus.  aPhotosynthesis.  aPlesiosauria.  aPraetor.  aPredation.  aPriam.  aProboscidea.  aProverb.  aRain.  aReptile.  aSalt.  aScreaming.  aSea turtle.  aSeawater.  aSirenia.  aSkeleton.  aSoft tissue.  aSoil salinity.  aSoil.  aStoicism.  aSurface water.  aTechnology.  aTerence.